        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43514",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "??I could not find any evidence for this statement.??\r\n\r\n[XHTML 1.0 - 4.10. The elements with 'id' and 'name' attributes|http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/xhtml1\/#h-4.10]\r\n\r\nI think the priority \"major\" is greatly exaggerated!",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-08T03:37:35.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-08T03:37:35.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43516",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=testvogel",
                        "name": "testvogel",
                        "displayName": "Marcus H\u00e4u\u00dfler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Thank you for the link, couldn't find this by myself :(\r\nI copied the priority from the source-ticket, so you are right.\r\n\r\n\r\nI thought HTML5 will be the future, not XHTML, any opinions?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=testvogel",
                        "name": "testvogel",
                        "displayName": "Marcus H\u00e4u\u00dfler",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-08T04:22:01.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-08T04:22:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43517",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ulfkirsten6",
                        "name": "ulfkirsten6",
                        "displayName": "Ulf Kirsten",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I strongly advise that HTML5 takes priority over XHTML. The simple reason: W3C declared XHTML as dead (http:\/\/www.w3.org\/2009\/06\/xhtml-faq.html). So the name atribute should be rendered by the ViewHelper of the form.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ulfkirsten6",
                        "name": "ulfkirsten6",
                        "displayName": "Ulf Kirsten",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-08T05:09:06.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-08T05:09:06.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43521",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mjh_ca",
                        "name": "mjh_ca",
                        "displayName": "Marc Hodgins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "It is possible to detect the DTD in use via the doctype view helper.  The view helpers are already doing this (i.e. deciding whether to include a closing \/ in tags), so look there for an example.  This should be fixable in a way that maintains compatibility with both HTML4, XHTML and HTML5",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=mjh_ca",
                        "name": "mjh_ca",
                        "displayName": "Marc Hodgins",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-08T10:52:17.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-08T10:52:17.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43535",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "100 points for *Marc*! :-)\r\n\r\nExample (not tested!):\r\n{code}\r\n\/**\r\n * Render HTML form\r\n *\r\n * @param  string $name Form name\r\n * @param  null|array $attribs HTML form attributes\r\n * @param  false|string $content Form content\r\n * @return string\r\n *\/\r\npublic function form($name, $attribs = null, $content = false)\r\n{\r\n    $info = $this->_getInfo($name, $content, $attribs);\r\n    extract($info);\r\n\r\n    \/\/ Set the id attribute if it exists\r\n    if (!empty($id)) {\r\n        $id = ' id=\"' . $this->view->escape($id) . '\"';\r\n    } else {\r\n        $id = '';\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    \/\/ Remove id from attributes\r\n    if (array_key_exists('id', $attribs) && empty($attribs['id'])) {\r\n        unset($attribs['id']);\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    \/\/ Set the name attribute if it exists and the doctype is not XHTML\r\n    if (false === $this->_isXhtml() && !empty($name)) {\r\n        $name = ' name=\"' . $this->view->escape($name) . '\"';\r\n    } else {\r\n        $name = '';\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    \/\/ Remove name from attributes\r\n    if (array_key_exists('name', $attribs) && empty($attribs['name'])) {\r\n        unset($attribs['name']);\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    $html = '<form'\r\n          . $id\r\n          . $name\r\n          . $this->_htmlAttribs($attribs)\r\n          . '>';\r\n\r\n    if (false !== $content) {\r\n        $html .= $content\r\n              .  '<\/form>';\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    return $html;\r\n}\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-09T02:41:19.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-09T03:01:01.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43594",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ulfkirsten6",
                        "name": "ulfkirsten6",
                        "displayName": "Ulf Kirsten",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I do not see the point why the attribute \"name\" should be removed when a xhtml doctype is set.\r\n\r\nThe W3C states in the XHTML 1.0 Recommendation taht the name attribute is formally deprecated and will be removes. As we all know there will be no future xhtml version and in the current 1.0 version it is allowed. Why then restrict the developer (especially under the fact that the older IE versions do not work properly and need the identical value for the \"name\"and \"id\" attribute)?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=ulfkirsten6",
                        "name": "ulfkirsten6",
                        "displayName": "Ulf Kirsten",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-14T09:47:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-14T09:47:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43660",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I agree with Ulf on this one.  XHTML 1.0 and 1.1 deprecated the name attribute on form tags but never formally removed it, and it is valid syntax in HTML5, so there is no reason to deny it's use here.\r\n\r\nI thought that you could do the following regardless of whether the name attribute is added by the view helper:\r\n{code}\r\n\/\/ When creating a new form instance\r\n$zf = new Zend_Form(array(\r\n    'attribs' => array(\r\n        'name' => 'NameOfForm'\r\n    )\r\n));\r\n\r\n\/\/ ...or inside the init() method of your Zend_Form subclass:\r\n$this->setAttrib('name', 'NameOfForm');\r\n{code}\r\nHowever, when I tried it against 1.11.1 it did not have the desired effect.  A change to Zend_View_Helper_Form like the one Kai suggested should fix that, though.   The other option would be to find out where in the call stack the name attribute is overridden (my money is on Zend_View_Helper_FormElement::_getInfo(..), but I haven't been able to prove that yet). ",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-17T08:38:52.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-17T08:40:24.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43662",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I've attached a patch which I think sorts out this issue:\r\n - single line change to Zend_View_Helper_FormElement::_getInfo(...)\r\n   (Allows overriding of name attribute on all Form elements)\r\n - Added two tests to Zend_View_Helper_FormTest ala the existing tests for the ID attribute\r\n\r\nComments?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-17T09:20:37.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-17T09:22:22.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43663",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Made a few slight changes\r\n - Fixed: Providing NULL name attribute should not produce <form name=\"\">\r\n - Added: Test to enforce above\r\n - Fixed: Nomenclature on tests was clumsy.  Changed to follow ID tests more closely.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
