                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "@Ulf & Adam\r\n??...in the current 1.0 version it is allowed.??\r\n??XHTML 1.0 and 1.1 deprecated the name attribute on form tags but never formally removed it??\r\n\r\nPlease carefully read the W3C-documents!\r\n\r\nOr use a validator. Example:\r\n{code}\r\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-\/\/W3C\/\/DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict\/\/EN\"\r\n     \"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/xhtml1\/DTD\/xhtml1-strict.dtd\">\r\n<html xmlns=\"http:\/\/www.w3.org\/1999\/xhtml\">\r\n<head>\r\n\t<title>Form test<\/title>\r\n\t<meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text\/html; charset=UTF-8\" \/>\r\n<\/head>\r\n<body>\r\n\t<form action=\"\" name=\"dummy\">\r\n\t<\/form>\r\n<\/body>\r\n<\/html>\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n[http:\/\/validator.w3.org]\r\n[http:\/\/www.validome.org]\r\n\r\n{quote}\r\nValidation Output: 1 Error\r\n\r\nLine 9, Column 23: there is no attribute \"name\"\r\n\r\nYou have used the attribute named above in your document, but the document type you are using does not support that attribute for this element. This error is often caused by incorrect use of the \"Strict\" document type with a document that uses frames (e.g. you must use the \"Transitional\" document type to get the \"target\" attribute), or by using vendor proprietary extensions such as \"marginheight\" (this is usually fixed by using CSS to achieve the desired effect instead).\r\n{quote}\r\n\r\nStill not convinced? ;-)\r\n\r\nLet's take a look at the DTD from XHTML 1.0 Strict: [http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/xhtml1\/dtds.html#a_dtd_XHTML-1.0-Strict]\r\n{code}\r\n<!ELEMENT form %form.content;>   <!-- forms shouldn't be nested -->\r\n\r\n<!ATTLIST form\r\n  %attrs;\r\n  action      %URI;          #REQUIRED\r\n  method      (get|post)     \"get\"\r\n  enctype     %ContentType;  \"application\/x-www-form-urlencoded\"\r\n  onsubmit    %Script;       #IMPLIED\r\n  onreset     %Script;       #IMPLIED\r\n  accept      %ContentTypes; #IMPLIED\r\n  accept-charset %Charsets;  #IMPLIED\r\n  >\r\n\r\n<!ENTITY % attrs \"%coreattrs; %i18n; %events;\">\r\n\r\n<!ENTITY % coreattrs\r\n \"id          ID             #IMPLIED\r\n  class       CDATA          #IMPLIED\r\n  style       %StyleSheet;   #IMPLIED\r\n  title       %Text;         #IMPLIED\"\r\n  >\r\n\r\n<!ENTITY % i18n\r\n \"lang        %LanguageCode; #IMPLIED\r\n  xml:lang    %LanguageCode; #IMPLIED\r\n  dir         (ltr|rtl)      #IMPLIED\"\r\n  >\r\n\r\n<!ENTITY % events\r\n \"onclick     %Script;       #IMPLIED\r\n  ondblclick  %Script;       #IMPLIED\r\n  onmousedown %Script;       #IMPLIED\r\n  onmouseup   %Script;       #IMPLIED\r\n  onmouseover %Script;       #IMPLIED\r\n  onmousemove %Script;       #IMPLIED\r\n  onmouseout  %Script;       #IMPLIED\r\n  onkeypress  %Script;       #IMPLIED\r\n  onkeydown   %Script;       #IMPLIED\r\n  onkeyup     %Script;       #IMPLIED\"\r\n  >\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nAnd now the DTD from XHTML 1.0 Transitional: [http:\/\/www.w3.org\/TR\/xhtml1\/dtds.html#a_dtd_XHTML-1.0-Transitional]\r\n{code}\r\n<!ELEMENT form %form.content;>   <!-- forms shouldn't be nested -->\r\n\r\n<!ATTLIST form\r\n  %attrs;\r\n  action      %URI;          #REQUIRED\r\n  method      (get|post)     \"get\"\r\n  name        NMTOKEN        #IMPLIED\r\n  enctype     %ContentType;  \"application\/x-www-form-urlencoded\"\r\n  onsubmit    %Script;       #IMPLIED\r\n  onreset     %Script;       #IMPLIED\r\n  accept      %ContentTypes; #IMPLIED\r\n  accept-charset %Charsets;  #IMPLIED\r\n  target      %FrameTarget;  #IMPLIED\r\n  >\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nYes, that's the difference between *Strict* and *Transitional*.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=kaiuwe",
                        "name": "kaiuwe",
                        "displayName": "Kai Uwe",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-12-18T04:45:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-12-18T04:49:18.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/43694",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Excellent point!  I failed to read the DTDs close enough, and took the W3C documents at their word that the element was deprecated and not removed.  Apologies for that.  I will modify my patch annd repost  later this morning.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=adamlundrigan",
                        "name": "adamlundrigan",
                        "displayName": "Adam Lundrigan",
